/target

# Rust build lockfile — this crate is a library, so we do
# not commit Cargo.lock. Anchored to the crate root so the
# `fuzz/` sub-crate (a binary) keeps its committed Cargo.lock,
# which cargo-fuzz expects to find.
# See https://doc.rust-lang.org/cargo/faq.html#why-do-binaries-have-cargolock-in-version-control-but-not-libraries
/Cargo.lock
